British armed forces are giving their support to secondary schools and colleges ahead of weekly nationwide testing for the coronavirus at educational establishments. A total of 1,500 Armed Forces staff are being made available to support Britain’s education and health departments to ensure students and staff can return to secondary schools and colleges across England safely, the Ministry of Defence said. Most of the military staff will offer support and advice over the phone and in virtual meetings, but some will be on standby to give in-person support to resolve any issues. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Department for Education announced two weeks ago that students and staff will be tested weekly at schools to help curb the rise in COVID-19 cases. Under the new scheme, students will be expected to swab themselves under the supervision of a school staff member or volunteer who has been trained. Uzbekistan Announces 2021 As Year Of Supporting Youth China’s Supreme Court Publishes 25 Typical Cases On State Compensation Teachers are not expected to take a role in the testing process. Schools in England are expected to reopen on Jan. 4 for the new spring term. However, a group of scientists that is advising the British government said schools should reopen later to keep rising infection rates under control, according to the Times newspaper. Dr Zubaida Haque, a member of the Independent Scientific Advisory Group for Emergencies (SAGE) group, said on Tuesday that it was not safe for schools to reopen as there is a “critical situation.” (dpa/NAN) SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION